20.5 securely synchronizing files

rsync is using ssh to synchronize files

if source and target files already exist, rsync will only sync the differences

the rsync has many options, these are the most common
	-r synchronizes recursively
	-l synchronizes symbolic links
	-p preserves symbolic links
	-n does a dry run before syncing
	-a uses archive mode, which is equivelant to -rlptgoD
	-A uses archive mode and also syncs ACLS
	-X will sync SELinux context as well
	
rsync -ar user@server:/target/ /destination/